[1] Case updates

- 16 Mar 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_16mar19?e=f96cddba3b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease dated 15 Mar 2019:

- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 943, of which 878 are confirmed and 65 are probable. In total, there have been 594 deaths (529 in confirmed and 65 in probable cases) and 311 people have recovered.
- 237 suspected cases under investigation;
- 7 new confirmed cases, including 2 in Kyondo, 2 in Katwa, 1 in Butembo, 1 in Masereka and 1 in Vuhovi;
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 2 community deaths, including 1 in Masereka and 1 in Katwa; 1 death at the Ebola treatment centre [ETC] Mabalako (this is a patient from Mandima);
- 1 new patient recovered out of ETC Butembo.

News of the response
--------------------
Vaccination

- Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 88 533 people have been vaccinated [See URL for number of vaccinees in each location.]

