- 15 Mar 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=bddce164c4

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease dated 14 Mar 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 936, 871 confirmed and 65 probable. In total, there have been 591 deaths (526 in confirmed and 65 in probable cases) and 310 people have recovered.
- 240 suspected cases under investigation;
- 4 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Mandima, 1 in Katwa, 1 in Butembo and 1 in Kayina;
- 4 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 2 community deaths, including 1 in Mandima and 1 in Butembo; 2 deaths at ETC, including 1 Mabalako and 1 in Beni (these are 2 cases reported to Mandima reported in the bulletin of Thu 14 Mar 2019);
- 1 new patient recovered out of ETC Butembo.

News of the response
--------------------
Vaccination

- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 88 360 people have been vaccinated [see URL for numbers of vaccines in each location].

