- Sat 16 Mar 2019. North Kivu: training of the 2nd Rapid Response Team against Ebola virus disease
[Digital Congo, online translation; abridged, edited]
https://digitalcongo.net/article/5c8cce43e7d83b000442dd62/

By the beginning of the week, Christophe Ndibeshe Byernero launched the training of the 29th Ebola Rapid Ebola Response Team at the Pallotine Missionary Center in Goma, North Kivu. Ndibeshe praised the support of WHO in building a multi-disciplinary team ready to be quickly deployed to any new outbreak of Ebola.

Forty health professionals made up of epidemiologists, laboratory technicians, psychiatrists, security specialists and experts in communication and social mobilization benefited from this training of the 29th Rapid Response Team against Ebola Virus Disease.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall

[It's great to see the training encompassing more than health care providers, but also psychiatrists, security specialists, and experts in communication and social mobilization. This multi-pronged approach is the most likely approach to be successful. - Mod.LK]

- Fri 15 Mar 2019. Ebola persistence; a shared responsibility between the population, the government, the CENI and the response team (LUCHA) [Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, abridged, edited]
http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5553

Persistence of Ebola virus disease in Butembo. The movement fights for change; LUCHA [Lutte pour le Changement; movement for change] breaks its silence. This citizen movement thinks that this responsibility is divided between population, government, CENI [Commission Électorale Nationale Indépendante; Independent National Electoral Commission] and the response team.

